  <!-- ============== INFO MODALS ============== -->
  <div id="info-modal-backdrop" class="info-modal-backdrop" hidden>
    <div class="info-modal" role="dialog" aria-modal="true">
      <button class="info-modal-close" aria-label="Close">×</button>

      <!-- About -->
      <section class="info-modal-content" data-info-content="about">
        <h2>About Json-Pi</h2>
        <p class="info-tagline">A fast, free, privacy-first toolkit for working with structured data.</p>

        <h3>What it is</h3>
        <p>Json-Pi is a browser-based application that lets developers and data analysts work with JSON, YAML, CSV, Excel, and PDF data without ever sending it to a server. Parse messy documents (with automatic repair of common syntax errors), convert between formats, extract structural insights, query with JSONPath, generate JSON Schemas, validate data, mock test records, and diff two documents — all in a single interface.</p>

        <h3>Who it's for</h3>
        <p>Backend developers debugging API responses, data engineers exploring unfamiliar data, QA engineers validating payloads, anyone who works with structured data and needs better tools than the browser DevTools console.</p>

        <h3>Key features</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Parse &amp; visualize</strong> JSON/YAML with auto-fix for common syntax errors</li>
          <li><strong>Convert tabular data</strong> (CSV/TSV/Excel) to JSON or YAML with smart shape detection</li>
          <li><strong>Explain structure</strong> with key-by-key breakdown and field-type inference</li>
          <li><strong>Find &amp; query</strong> with JSONPath syntax</li>
          <li><strong>Convert</strong> between JSON and YAML</li>
          <li><strong>JSON Schema</strong> generation, validation, and mock data generation</li>
          <li><strong>Diff</strong> two documents with side-by-side, unified, or path-only views</li>
          <li><strong>Developer API</strong> — every UI feature is also a REST endpoint</li>
          <li><strong>Light &amp; dark themes</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Privacy promise</h3>
        <p>Json-Pi runs entirely in your browser. The only data that ever leaves your device is what you explicitly submit through the Contact form. There is no analytics, no tracking, no cookies, no account, no telemetry. The "Developer API" endpoints accept text you send them but do not store it.</p>

        <h3>How issues are handled</h3>
        <p>If you find a bug, have a feature request, or want to give feedback, please use the <button class="info-link" data-info-modal="contact">Contact</button> form. Submissions go directly to the developer; you'll get a reply within a few days.</p>

        <h3>Tech credits</h3>
        <p>Json-Pi uses these excellent open-source libraries: <code>js-yaml</code> (YAML parsing), <code>PapaParse</code> (CSV parsing), <code>SheetJS</code> (Excel files), <code>PDF.js</code> (PDF text extraction), <code>jsPDF</code> (PDF generation). The backend runs on Netlify Functions; contact submissions are stored via Supabase.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section class="info-modal-content" data-info-content="contact">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Found a bug? Have a suggestion? Want to say hi? Drop a message below — it goes straight to the developer.</p>

        <form id="contact-form" class="contact-form" novalidate>
          <label>
            <span class="contact-label">Name <span class="contact-optional">(optional)</span></span>
            <input type="text" id="contact-name" name="name" maxlength="100" autocomplete="name" />
          </label>
          <label>
            <span class="contact-label">Email <span class="contact-optional">(optional — leave blank to remain anonymous)</span></span>
            <input type="email" id="contact-email" name="email" maxlength="120" autocomplete="email" />
          </label>
          <label>
            <span class="contact-label">Subject <span class="contact-required">*</span></span>
            <input type="text" id="contact-subject" name="subject" maxlength="200" required />
          </label>
          <label>
            <span class="contact-label">Message <span class="contact-required">*</span></span>
            <textarea id="contact-message" name="message" rows="6" maxlength="5000" required></textarea>
            <span class="contact-char-count"><span id="contact-char-count">0</span> / 5000</span>
          </label>
          <!-- Honeypot field — hidden from real users, bots will fill it -->
          <input type="text" id="contact-website" name="website" class="honeypot" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off" />

          <div id="contact-form-status"></div>

          <div class="contact-form-actions">
            <button type="button" class="btn-ghost" id="btn-contact-cancel">Cancel</button>
            <button type="submit" class="btn-primary" id="btn-contact-submit">Send message</button>
          </div>
        </form>

        <p class="contact-note">Direct email: <code id="contact-email-display">contact via form</code> — we obfuscate the public email to reduce spam.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Terms -->
